---
name: dataset-of
---

# Dataset.of — basic round-trip

`Dataset.of(...)` wraps in-memory values; `.collect()` returns them as a
list; `.count()` returns the size; plan is reusable.

```scalascript
val ds = Dataset.of(1, 2, 3, 4, 5)

println(ds.collect().mkString(", "))
println(ds.count())

// Reuse — two terminals on the same Dataset
println(ds.reduce(_ + _))
println(ds.first().getOrElse(-1))
```
